  <summary date="2023-06-07T19:41:29Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Credit Union Board Modernization Act 

This bill revises the required frequency of meetings held by a credit union's board of directors. Specifically, new credit unions and credit unions with a low soundness rating must meet monthly. All other credit unions must hold at least six meetings annually, with at least one meeting held during each fiscal quarter. Currently, all credit union boards must meet at least once a month.</summary>
